rm and Miraculous Cures Christian Healing and AIDS in New Ireland, Papua New Guinea -- t12. SikAIDS Deconstructing the Awareness Campaign in Rural West New Britain, Papua New Guinea -- t13. Fitting Condoms on Culture Rethinking Approaches to HIV Prevention in the Trobriand Islands, Papua New Guinea -- tNotes -- tBibliography -- tContributors -- tIndex -- tAbout the Editors0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIn Melanesia, rates of HIV infection are among the highest in the Pacific and increasing rapidly, with grave humanitarian, development, and political implications. There is a great need for social research on HIV/AIDS in the region to provide better insights into the sensitive issues surrounding HIV transmission. This collection, the first book on HIV and AIDS in the Pacific region, gathers together stunning and original accounts of the often surprising ways that people make sense of the AIDS epidemic in various parts of Melanesia. The volume addresses substantive issues concerning AIDS and contemporary sexualities, relations of power, and moralities—themes that provide a powerful backdrop for twenty-first century understandings of the tensions between sexuality, religion, and politics in many parts of the world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aAIDS (Disease)xReligious aspects. 0aAIDS (Disease)xSocial aspectszMelanesia. 0aAIDS (Disease)zMelanesia. 7aHEALTH & FITNESS / Diseases / AIDS & HIV.2bisacsh1 aBeer, Bettina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuchanan-Aruwafu, Holly, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aButt, Leslie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aButt, Leslie, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1